    "attributes": {
        "action": "Change the law so people with learning disabilities or autism can\u2019t be detained",
        "additional_details": "People with learning disabilities or autism should have bespoke packages of support to achieve a better outcome rather than being locked away in these institutions. Following the Winterbourne Review the Government promised to move all those with learning disabilities and/or autism inappropriately placed in such institutions into community care. We should go further and stop the detention of such people entirely.",
        "background": "I would like to put an end to people with learning disabilities or autism being detained in hospital under the Mental Health Act.",
